var textForPages =["","Content\u000d\u000a1. Message by Santhosh Viswanathan, Vice \u000d\u000aPresident & Managing Director, India Region, Intel\u000d\u000a2. Message by Sarah Kemp, Vice President , \u000d\u000aInternational Government Affairs, Intel\u000d\u000a3. About Intel Digital Readiness Programs in India\u000d\u000a4. Impact of Intel Digital Readiness Programs in India\u000d\u000a5. AI Innovations by students\u000d\u000aA. Impact stories from K12 education\u000d\u000aB. Impact stories from higher education\u000d\u000a6. Impact stories from the AI for All program","This compendium of AI Impact stories highlights progress, not just potential. It covers classrooms gaining digital \u000d\u000ainfrastructure, to youth learning to create AI-based solutions, to startups innovating with affordable, frugal AI solutions. \u000d\u000aThe journeys reflect a shared roadmap where policymakers, educators, innovators and the private sector align to make \u000d\u000aaccess real, skills meaningful and growth truly equitable.\u000d\u000aToday what we are witnessing is not just technological change - but societal transformation. We are proud to stand at \u000d\u000athis intersection, committed to an India where every learner, every educator and every community is empowered for the \u000d\u000aAI\u2010powered future.\u000d\u000aSanthosh Viswanathan\u000d\u000aVice President & Managing Director, \u000d\u000aIndia Region, Intel\u000d\u000aMESSAGE \u000d\u000aIndia is at a once-in-a-generation moment in our digital journey. In an era shaped \u000d\u000aby artificial intelligence, the question is no longer simply how we innovate but \u000d\u000awho we enable. Every student deserves the chance to participate, contribute \u000d\u000aand thrive in this new reality. At Intel, we believe that digital infrastructure, device \u000d\u000aaccess, and AI fluency are not privileges, but fundamentals!\u000d\u000aA digitally empowered India is one in which students become knowledge \u000d\u000acreators with access to relevant infrastructure, educators have access to AI \u000d\u000atools to inspire better learning outcomes, and even remote schools have reliable \u000d\u000aconnectivity - where technology is not just available, but meaningful, accessible, \u000d\u000aand relevant.","Our journey would not be possible without our valued partners across government, academia, and civil society. Their leadership and \u000d\u000avision have helped create pathways of access - from connectivity to devices and learning resources, ensuring that AI readiness \u000d\u000aextends beyond classrooms and cities to every corner of the nation.\u000d\u000aTogether, we have expanded into underserved regions and empowered millions of students, educators, professionals, and citizens to \u000d\u000aactively contribute to India\u2019s digital economy. These collective efforts are building the foundation of an AI-ready India - one that is \u000d\u000ainclusive, innovative, and future-forward.\u000d\u000aAs we look ahead, Intel remains deeply committed to strengthening partnerships, closing access gaps, and advancing AI skilling \u000d\u000aacross communities. Together, we can shape a future where technology truly empowers everyone, everywhere!\u000d\u000aSarah Kemp\u000d\u000aVice President, International\u000d\u000aGovernment Affairs,\u000d\u000aIntel Corporation\u000d\u000aMessage\u000d\u000aAt Intel, we believe Digital Readiness is the cornerstone of inclusive growth in the AI \u000d\u000aera. True progress is not defined by technology alone - it\u2019s about ensuring that every \u000d\u000acitizen has equitable access to relevant digital infrastructure, the confidence to use \u000d\u000atechnology responsibly, and the opportunity to participate meaningfully in an AIpowered future.\u000d\u000aThrough our Digital Readiness programs, we are translating this belief into action. \u000d\u000aDesigned to reach diverse, non-technical audiences, these initiatives build the \u000d\u000amindsets, skillsets, and opportunities needed to thrive in a rapidly evolving world. By \u000d\u000acombining awareness, skilling, and access, we are nurturing a generation that sees AI \u000d\u000anot as a challenge, but as a tool for empowerment.","BUILDING\u000d\u000aDIGITAL READINESS\u000d\u000aIN INDIA\u000d\u000aIntel is driving AI empowerment in India through a technology-focused \u000d\u000aapproach that integrates AI into educational curricula, offers \u000d\u000amentorship, and advances skill-building initiatives to close the AI skills \u000d\u000agap. Our shared value, shared responsibility initiative, Intel\u00ae Digital \u000d\u000aReadiness Programs portfolio, spans across 29 countries and is \u000d\u000aexecuted in collaboration with governments and academia. It is \u000d\u000adesigned to demystify and democratize emerging technologies like AI, \u000d\u000aensuring inclusive access for all.","Intel\u00ae AI for Youth\u000d\u000aThe program advances AI readiness in K12 \u000d\u000aeducation sectors in collaboration with Central \u000d\u000aBoard of Secondary Education (CBSE), Atal \u000d\u000aInnovation Mission (AIM), NITI Aayog and \u000d\u000aDepartment of Science and Technology (DST) \u000d\u000aon national AI innovation platforms. The initiative \u000d\u000asupports teachers and students by introducing \u000d\u000aAI as a formal subject, training educators, and \u000d\u000aproviding mentorship.","Intel partnered with over 600 higher education institutions to equip students with \u000d\u000aessential AI skills for employability in the digital economy. Institutions introduced \u000d\u000asector-specific AI courses aligned with local needs.\u000d\u000aAdvancing Organic Farming through AI Education in Nagaland\u000d\u000aIntel introduced the AI for Agriculture certificate program at the Institute of\u000d\u000aCommunication and IT, Mokokchung, Nagaland, in alignment with state government's vision to \u000d\u000aadvance organic farming practices. This initiative equipped students with AI skills to enhance \u000d\u000asustainable agricultural methods.\u000d\u000aShaping the Future of Manufacturing in Gujarat\u000d\u000aThe AI for Manufacturing course, offered as an elective at Gujarat Technological University \u000d\u000aand supported by Intel and the Gujarat Chamber of Commerce & Industry (GCCI), saw over \u000d\u000a1,500 students from 60+ colleges undergo 14-week summer training and submit 831 projects \u000d\u000atackling real-world challenges to support the manufacturing sector. Through collaborations \u000d\u000awith industry partners, students engaged in real-world manufacturing projects, gaining \u000d\u000ahands-on experience that bridged academic learning with practical application.\u000d\u000aAt GTU, we believe AI is central to the future of manufacturing. In \u000d\u000apartnership with Intel India and the GCCI, we\u2019ve launched the Intel AI for \u000d\u000aManufacturing course across 60+ affiliated colleges. This is more than a \u000d\u000acurriculum upgrade \u2014 it is a strategic investment in the future, empowering \u000d\u000astudents to apply AI to real-world industrial challenges through hands-on, \u000d\u000aproject-based learning. It\u2019s a step to strengthen Gujarat\u2019s innovation \u000d\u000aecosystem and build a future-ready, tech-enabled workforce.\u000d\u000a~ Dr. Mihir SHah, Advisor (Skill Education),\u000d\u000a GTU Venture, Gujarat Technological University\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI for\u000d\u000aFuture Workforce","Empowering Educators to Build India\u2019s AI-ready Workforce\u000d\u000aIntel, in collaboration with the National Institute of Technical Teachers \u000d\u000aTraining and Research (NITTTR) Chandigarh, one of the Ministry of \u000d\u000aEducation\u2019s key training centers delivered a comprehensive Faculty \u000d\u000aDevelopment Program for 300 educators from 170+ technical colleges \u000d\u000aacross India.\u000d\u000aThe program equipped faculty with cutting-edge knowledge and skills in \u000d\u000aAI, machine learning, applied ethics, and data-centric AI through \u000d\u000ainteractive sessions and hands-on labs. This initiative, based on Intel\u2019s AI \u000d\u000afor Future Workforce program, is empowering educators to integrate \u000d\u000aadvanced AI concepts into technical education, driving innovation and \u000d\u000apreparing a future-ready workforce at scale.\u000d\u000aThe program is designed to demystify AI and make it accessible to people \u000d\u000afrom all walks of life. It is available in 11 Indian languages and includes \u000d\u000aaccessibility features for individuals with learning disabilities via TalkBack \u000d\u000aapplications. The outreach extended to forming 720 local groups and \u000d\u000atraining more than 10,000 citizens in rural areas, with 350 women AI \u000d\u000afacilitators engaged in Bihar\u2019s Edu-Leaders fellowship program, fostering \u000d\u000agrassroots empowerment through AI education.\u000d\u000aTechnology is for everyone\u2014knowledge knows no \u000d\u000aage. Seeing my village embrace AI has inspired \u000d\u000ame to keep spreading awareness and empower \u000d\u000apeople with the tools to shape their future.\u000d\u000a~ Kajal, Edu-Leader Fellow, Munger, Bihar\u000d\u000aI never imagined I\u2019d be the one to introduce AI to \u000d\u000amy village. The first time I explained artificial \u000d\u000aintelligence, I talked with joy about how AI powers \u000d\u000athe weather app on our phones. Everyone looked \u000d\u000aamazed. It\u2019s moments like these that make me feel \u000d\u000aproud to be part of this journey.\u000d\u000a~ Rupa, Jamui, Bihar\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI for Citizens","Intel\u00ae Digital Readiness Programs in India\u000d\u000aTo demystify and democratize \u000d\u000aemerging technologies for broader \u000d\u000anon-technical audiences, the Intel\u00ae \u000d\u000aDigital Readiness Program portfolio \u000d\u000ahas been rolled out in the country, in \u000d\u000acollaboration with governments, \u000d\u000aacademia, civil society, and industry.\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI for\u000d\u000aCitizens\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI for Youth\u000d\u000aEmpower youth with AI tech and \u000d\u000asocial skills in an inclusive way.\u000d\u000aTo date, we have empowered\u000d\u000a24 lakh students,\u000d\u000a10,000+ institutions\u000d\u000awith the relevant AI tech and social skills \u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI for Future \u000d\u000aWorkforce\u000d\u000aEmpower future workforce with AI skills for \u000d\u000aemployability in the digital economy.\u000d\u000aTo date, we have empowered\u000d\u000a22,000+ students, 1882+ educators\u000d\u000a600+ institutions\u000d\u000aDemystify AI for the public and community.\u000d\u000aTo date, we have empowered\u000d\u000a50 lakh citizens","Digital Readiness = Digital Skills + Trust + Responsible Use\u000d\u000ascan the\u000d\u000aQR code to\u000d\u000aknow more \u000d\u000aEducate and empower government \u000d\u000aleaders on emerging technologies\u000d\u000aTo date, we have empowered\u000d\u000a5400+ government officials\u000d\u000a40 government departments\u000d\u000aDemocratize and celebrate AI Innovation \u000d\u000awith Intel by next-gen technologists and \u000d\u000afuture developers\u000d\u000aTo date, we have empowered\u000d\u000a1,13,386 students and professionals\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI Global \u000d\u000aImpact Festival\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae Digital\u000d\u000aReadiness for Leaders\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae AI for\u000d\u000aCurrent Workforce\u000d\u000aEnable and augment existing workforce \u000d\u000acapacity with AI skills for work and life impact\u000d\u000aTo date, we have empowered\u000d\u000a417+ government officials\u000d\u000a5 government departments","YOUNG\u000d\u000aINNOVATORS\u000d\u000aUshering social change\u000d\u000awith AI","FOR A YOUTH\u000d\u000aK12 EDUCATION","At just 13, Aadit Kashyap, a grade 8 student at Delhi Public School, Nacharam, Telangana, is \u000d\u000aproving that innovation is about people. While most teenagers focus on games and \u000d\u000agadgets, Aadit turned his attention to something deeper\u2014the silent struggles of children \u000d\u000aon the autism spectrum.\u000d\u000aPained by their isolation, he designed DigiFriend, an AI-powered companion that listens, \u000d\u000aunderstands, and provides a safe space for children who feel unheard. Unlike conventional \u000d\u000achatbots that only respond to words, DigiFriend senses \u000d\u000aemotions by analyzing facial expressions and voice tones \u000d\u000ausing advanced machine learning models. Integrated with a \u000d\u000asmart band and a parent-side application, DigiFriend creates \u000d\u000aa holistic support system that ensures every child has the \u000d\u000asupport they need to navigate their world with confidence.\u000d\u000aDIGIFRIEND\u000d\u000aAI THAT LISTENS, LEARNS,\u000d\u000aAND EMPOWERS,\u000d\u000aMISSION TO HELP\u000d\u000aAUTISTIC CHILDREN\u000d\u000aAadit Kashyap\u000d\u000aDelhi Public School,\u000d\u000aHyderabad, \u000d\u000aTelangana","Aadit Kashyap created DigiFriend\u2014\u000d\u000aan AI-powered ally that understands \u000d\u000aemotions, offering children on the \u000d\u000aautism spectrum a voice, a friend, \u000d\u000aand a safe space to thrive.\u000d\u000aAadit\u2019s journey began with a childhood curiosity sparked by \u000d\u000awatching his father work with spreadsheets. This curiosity \u000d\u000aquickly developed into a deep passion for computers, which was \u000d\u000afurther honed when he enrolled in the Intel AI for Youth program.\u000d\u000aThe program, which provided him with structured knowledge, \u000d\u000amarked the beginning of a transformative chapter in his life. \u000d\u000aThrough immersive AI boot camps and mentorship from experts, \u000d\u000aAadit gained technical expertise, and an understanding of the \u000d\u000aprofound impact innovation can have on society. \u201cAI helped me \u000d\u000afocus on purposeful action,\u201d Aadit recalls. \u201cIt showed me how \u000d\u000atechnology can improve life for those who really need it.\u201d \u000d\u000aDigiFriend quickly gained recognition, with Aadit winning the \u000d\u000aIndia AI Impact Festival 2024 and presenting his project at the \u000d\u000aAMCHAM Conference, hosted by the American Chamber of \u000d\u000aCommerce.\u000d\u000aFor Aadit, though, the true reward lies in transforming lives. He\u2019s \u000d\u000apiloting DigiFriend at an NGO in Hyderabad and plans to expand \u000d\u000aits features to support teens dealing with stress and anxiety.\u000d\u000aIn an age where AI often feels impersonal, Aadit Kashyap is \u000d\u000arewriting the narrative. He\u2019s building a world where no child feels \u000d\u000aalone, proving that the most powerful technology is the kind that \u000d\u000aspeaks the language of the heart.","Teena Sahu had witnessed the crippling effects of depression \u000d\u000afirsthand\u2014the silent struggles, the pressure to fit in, and the \u000d\u000auncertainty of growing up. In 2019, while in grade 11, she and her two \u000d\u000afriends were deeply troubled by the alarming rise in teenage \u000d\u000adepression and suicides. They knew something had to be done.\u000d\u000aTeena Sahu\u2019s lifesaving innovation \u000d\u000atransforms teenage mental health support \u000d\u000athrough early detection and timely \u000d\u000aintervention. \u000d\u000aHAPPINESS\u000d\u000aGURU\u000d\u000aA BEACON OF\u000d\u000aHOPE FOR YOUTH\u000d\u000aMENTAL HEALTH\u000d\u000aTeena Sahu\u000d\u000aSalwan Girls Sr. \u000d\u000aSec. School, \u000d\u000aNew Delhi","Intel's AI for Youth program became a turning point. Despite studying in a government-aided school \u000d\u000awith limited technology exposure, this program introduced Teena to AI's power in solving real-world \u000d\u000achallenges. She envisioned Happiness Guru, an AI-driven model to detect early signs of depression \u000d\u000aand alert teachers and guardians before it was too late. \u000d\u000aDetermined to build a data-backed solution, the team surveyed over \u000d\u000a700 students aged 14-16 across five schools. Using computer vision \u000d\u000aand natural language processing, Happiness Guru analyzed facial \u000d\u000aexpressions to identify distress signs. The AI model, trained on the \u000d\u000aCohn\u2013Kanade Facial Expression dataset, categorized emotions as \u000d\u000ahappy, sad, neutral, or angry. Students also completed \u000d\u000aself-assessment questionnaires, with an SVM-based classification \u000d\u000amodel processing text responses to detect negative thought \u000d\u000apatterns.\u000d\u000aWith 77-80% accuracy, Happiness Guru served as an early-warning \u000d\u000asystem, helping educators intervene before crises unfolded. Teena's \u000d\u000ainnovation earned her a full scholarship to study AI Ethics and Law \u000d\u000awhile shaping her life's purpose.\u000d\u000a\u201cIntel\u2019s AI for Youth program gave me the tools to turn an idea into reality. It helped me navigate the \u000d\u000atech world and discover my passion for AI. Today, I dream of creating AI solutions that make a real \u000d\u000aimpact\u2014just like Happiness Guru did,\u201d says Teena.\u000d\u000aTeena now envisions scaling Happiness Guru to reach more schools and mental health professionals, ensuring no student suffers \u000d\u000ain silence. Her journey is a testament that technology isn't just about progress\u2014it\u2019s about saving lives.","The seed of Trikona AI was planted when \u000d\u000aDeepanshu, a 9th-grade student, pondered while \u000d\u000alearning Pythagoras' theorem: \"Will I ever use this in \u000d\u000areal life?\" This wasn't just a fleeting thought but a \u000d\u000ayearning to bridge theory and tangible reality. \u000d\u000aDuring the 2020 pandemic, Deepanshu began \u000d\u000aexploring AI development. Combining his \u000d\u000afascination with triangles and AI, he created Trikona \u000d\u000aAI\u2014named after the Sanskrit word for \"triangle.\"\u000d\u000aAccurate angle and dimension measurements are \u000d\u000acrucial in architecture and construction, yet \u000d\u000atraditional methods are time-consuming and \u000d\u000aerror-prone. Deepanshu's solution: a web-based \u000d\u000aapplication that simplifies this process.\u000d\u000aDEEPANSHU AND\u000d\u000aTRIKONA AI\u000d\u000aTHE\u000d\u000aTRIANGLE\u000d\u000aOF DREAMS\u000d\u000aFrom a classroom question to a world of \u000d\u000apossibilities\u2014how Deepanshu blended Math, \u000d\u000aAI, and imagination to reshape precision \u000d\u000ameasurement.\u000d\u000aDeepanshu Jha\u000d\u000aDr. Rajendra Prasad\u000d\u000aKendriya Vidyalaya,\u000d\u000aDelhi","Trikona AI uses advanced computer vision powered by \u000d\u000aOpenCV. Users visit the website, point their camera, and \u000d\u000aselect key points. The app then performs complex \u000d\u000atrigonometric calculations, accurately measures angles, \u000d\u000aand calculates sine, cosine, tangent, and hypotenuse \u000d\u000avalues. Besides streamlining architectural work, it's also \u000d\u000aa robust educational tool for visualizing abstract \u000d\u000amathematical concepts.\u000d\u000aDeepanshu was in grade 8 when his journey gained \u000d\u000amomentum thanks to India\u2019s first AI Skills Lab at his \u000d\u000aschool. There, he refined his ideas through insightful \u000d\u000adiscussions and mentorship. However, without a \u000d\u000apowerful PC, developing AI applications felt like an uphill \u000d\u000aclimb. angle in his triangle of dreams.\u000d\u000aHowever, enrolling for Intel\u2019s AI for Youth program in January 2024 was \u000d\u000alife-transforming for him. He got access to cutting-edge hardware, expert \u000d\u000amentors, and immersive bootcamps, which enabled him to hone Trikona AI, \u000d\u000ashowcase it on multiple platforms, and earn enthusiastic feedback.\u000d\u000aNow in 10th grade, Deepanshu stands at the threshold of revolutionizing \u000d\u000aprecision measurement by making Trikona AI widely accessible and refining \u000d\u000aits accuracy. For this young visionary, Trikona AI isn't just a project; it's the first ","In 2019, Yash Yadav began his journey with basic \u000d\u000aprogramming, but the Intel AI Boot Camp in 2021 \u000d\u000atransformed his path. While his knowledge had been limited \u000d\u000ato HTML, the boot camp introduced him to AI and Python, \u000d\u000aproviding both conceptual understanding and practical \u000d\u000aproject experience\u000d\u000aAs Yash delved deeper into science, he couldn\u2019t ignore an \u000d\u000aunsettling truth. In his high school class of 50, only seven \u000d\u000awere girls. Curious, he dug deeper.\u000d\u000aBREAKING\u000d\u000aGENDER\u000d\u000aBARRIERS\u000d\u000aIN STEM WITH STEMLY\u000d\u000aHarnessing AI to ensure every girl can dream big, \u000d\u000alearn fearlessly, and stay in STEM.\u000d\u000aYash Yadav\u000d\u000aMKH Sancheti Public\u000d\u000aSchool, Nagpur,\u000d\u000aMaharashtra","UNESCO reports show only 28% of STEM graduates \u0101worldwide are women, with India\u2019s numbers even lower. \u000d\u000aMcKinsey highlights the need for more women in STEM, while Nobel Prize data shows just 0.05% of laureates \u000d\u000ain STEM fields are female. Conversations with classmates painted a clearer picture\u2014societal expectations and \u000d\u000ainternal doubts were silently pushing many girls out of STEM.\u000d\u000aArmed with the knowledge gained from the Intel AI Boot Camp, Yash developed STEMLY, an AI-driven web \u000d\u000aplatform designed to empower young women in STEM. Like an AI mentor, STEMLY engages in conversation, \u000d\u000aassesses their interests, detects waning enthusiasm using natural language processing (NLP), and intervenes \u000d\u000awith motivational stories and practical advice. Further, by tracking progress and refining responses over time, \u000d\u000aSTEMLY ensures personalized, meaningful support. \u000d\u000a\"The Intel AI Boot Camp was crucial\u2014I gained insights into AI concepts, \u000d\u000aproject design, and implementation,\" Yash explains. His innovation has \u000d\u000aearned global recognition, winning Intel's Global AI Impact Festival 2023 \u000d\u000aand Samsung's Solve for Tomorrow competition. Beta testing has \u000d\u000aalready encouraged several female students to reconsider\u000d\u000aSTEM careers.\u000d\u000aNow, Yash is enhancing STEMLY\u2019s accuracy while also working on an \u000d\u000aAI-driven cybersecurity project to counter corporate social engineering \u000d\u000aattacks. Aspiring to launch a startup, he envisions a world where \u201cevery \u000d\u000agirl can pursue what she wants, free from societal or mental barriers.\u201d \u000d\u000aThrough STEMLY, Yash isn\u2019t just building technology\u2014he\u2019s rewriting the \u000d\u000afuture for women in STEM.","In a world where mental health struggles often remain invisible, \u000d\u000a14-year-old Himank Arora is making the unseen seen through \u000d\u000aartificial intelligence. While most teenagers explore technology \u000d\u000afor entertainment, this young innovator has transformed it into a \u000d\u000ashield for the vulnerable.\u000d\u000aCODING\u000d\u000aCOMPASSION\u000d\u000aHIMANK ARORA\u2019S AI SOLUTION\u000d\u000aFOR MENTAL HEALTH\u000d\u000aA teenage innovator creates an AI guardian \u000d\u000aangel for those battling depression, turning \u000d\u000atechnology into a lifeline of hope.\u000d\u000aHimank Arora\u000d\u000aDAV \u000d\u000aMultipurpose\u000d\u000aSchool, Sonipat,\u000d\u000aHaryana","Himank\u2019s technological journey began during the COVID lockdown. \u000d\u000a\u201cAs a 5th grader, I was surrounded by technology, with both my \u000d\u000amother and aunt being computer teachers,\u201d he recalls. What started \u000d\u000aas curious glances at programming notes soon blossomed into a \u000d\u000apassion with purpose.\u000d\u000aThe pivotal moment came in April 2022 when Himank joined Intel\u2019s \u000d\u000aAI for Youth boot camp. His understanding expanded beyond basic \u000d\u000acoding into deep learning and neural networks. Inspired, Himank \u000d\u000acreated an AI monitoring system for patients with Major Depressive \u000d\u000aDisorder (MDD). His innovation combines a wearable band that \u000d\u000atracks oxygen levels and audio cues with AI that analyzes facial \u000d\u000aexpressions and speech patterns to detect emotional distress. \u000d\u000aWhen the system identifies crisis moments, it immediately alerts \u000d\u000acaregivers and medical professionals, potentially saving lives.\u000d\u000aThe technology achieves 92% accuracy in emotion detection, while \u000d\u000aadaptive algorithms assess emotional states holistically.\u000d\u000aThe wearable also includes vibration therapy, inspired by Harvard \u000d\u000aresearch, which stimulates dopamine release to help calm patients \u000d\u000ain distress.\u000d\u000aWorking with six doctors, Himank has tested his system on 54 \u000d\u000apatients, earning national recognition, including a meeting with \u000d\u000aIndia\u2019s Prime Minister Narendra Modi at Pariksha Pe Charcha 2024.\u000d\u000aNow in Grade 9, Himank continues refining his project while \u000d\u000aconsidering a future in aerospace engineering. His heart, \u000d\u000ahowever, remains committed to using AI as a force for good. \u000d\u000a\u201cUse AI responsibly,\u201d he advises young innovators, \u201cand join \u000d\u000aprograms like Intel AI for Youth to unlock your potential.\u201d\u000d\u000aIn Himank\u2019s hands, algorithms have become more than\u000d\u000acode\u2014they\u2019ve become companions for those walking \u000d\u000athrough their darkest hours.","Growing up in Haridwar, a city known for its spiritual \u000d\u000aheritage and Ayurvedic traditions, Aviral had always \u000d\u000abeen surrounded by the healing power of herbs. But \u000d\u000ait wasn't until one night when he suffered a severe \u000d\u000astomachache that the idea for Herbalens truly took \u000d\u000aroot. In the absence of medication, his mother picked \u000d\u000aherbs from their kitchen garden and brewed a simple \u000d\u000aconcoction. Magically, the pain faded within minutes. \u000d\u000aThat night, Aviral realized something powerful\u2014\u000d\u000anature had the answers, but not everyone knew how \u000d\u000ato find them.\u000d\u000aIdentifying medicinal herbs accurately is no easy \u000d\u000atask. Many plants, like peppermint and pennyroyal, \u000d\u000aappear deceptively similar, leading to confusion and \u000d\u000apotential risk. Ayurvedic practitioners and herbal \u000d\u000aenthusiasts often lack the tools for precise \u000d\u000aidentification, leaving nature\u2019s gifts underutilized.\u000d\u000aAVIRAL\u000d\u000aTHE\u000d\u000aJOURNEY OF\u000d\u000aHERBALENS\u000d\u000aCoding nature's secrets: How a kitchen garden cure evolved into \u000d\u000aan AI-powered healing remedy","Aviral, who began coding in 2022, envisioned Herbalens as an AI-powered app \u000d\u000abridging traditional knowledge and modern technology. Built with HTML, CSS, \u000d\u000aand JavaScript, users simply take a picture, and the app analyzes leaf \u000d\u000acharacteristics to provide instant identification, offering detailed medicinal uses, \u000d\u000asafety guidelines, and personalized remedies.\u000d\u000aThe innovation employs machine learning algorithms enhanced by user inputs \u000d\u000aand plant databases. It even integrates environmental factors and user location to \u000d\u000arecommend nearby botanical gardens where required plants can be found.\u000d\u000aAviral\u2019s innovation flourished with mentorship from Intel\u2019s AI program. After \u000d\u000aclinching second place at the Uttaranchal Hackathon in May 2024, he advanced \u000d\u000ato the Intel India AI Impact Festival, where he showcased Herbalens to industry \u000d\u000aleaders. \u201cThe guidance I received helped me transform an idea into a real \u000d\u000asolution,\u201d says Aviral. \u000d\u000aCurrently, in 8th grade, Aviral aims to refine Herbalens, secure a patent, and \u000d\u000aintegrate an e-commerce platform for customized remedies. He dreams of a \u000d\u000afuture where Herbalens empowers people to harness the healing power of \u000d\u000anature, ensuring safe and sustainable practices.\u000d\u000aAviral Tyagi\u000d\u000aD.A.V Centenary\u000d\u000aPublic School,\u000d\u000aHaridwar,\u000d\u000aUttarakhand","Krish was a curious teenager when his AI journey \u000d\u000abegan in 2020. Though he\u2019d always loved coding, \u000d\u000aartificial intelligence seemed out of reach until he \u000d\u000ajoined the AI Student Community (AISC). \u201cEverything \u000d\u000awas taught weekly, and there were a lot of practice \u000d\u000aopportunities,\u201d Krish recalls. By early 2021, he was \u000d\u000aimmersed in AI challenges and boot camps, \u000d\u000asharpening both skill and confidence.\u000d\u000aBHASHA X\u000d\u000aKRISH'S QUEST TO\u000d\u000aGLOBALIZE CODING\u000d\u000aA teen\u2019s mission to make coding accessible for \u000d\u000aall\u2014transforming language barriers into \u000d\u000aopportunities with AI-powered code translation.\u000d\u000aKrish Yadav\u000d\u000aMKH Sancheti Public\u000d\u000aSchool, Nagpur,\u000d\u000aMaharashtra","The spark of innovation struck during a coding competition when \u000d\u000aa peer complained that programming resources were \u000d\u000apredominantly in English. \"Even with Hindi explanations, \u000d\u000aunderstanding the code was difficult,\" the student confessed. \u000d\u000aKrish dug deeper and discovered a UNESCO report that \u000d\u000aemphasized the importance of mother-tongue learning for true \u000d\u000ainclusion. His survey confirmed it: 76% of developers preferred \u000d\u000atheir native language to better understand code.\u000d\u000aDetermined to bridge this gap, Krish developed BhashaX Code \u000d\u000aSummarizer, an AI-powered tool that translates and explains \u000d\u000acode in a developer\u2019s native language. It uses a \u000d\u000asequence-to-sequence model with self-attention, optimized by \u000d\u000aIntel\u2019s OpenVINO runtime. BhashaX can convert code \u000d\u000aexplanations into multiple languages and integrates directly with \u000d\u000acoding platforms as a real-time IDE extension.\u000d\u000aIntel's AI for Youth program provided the mentorship Krish needed. His heart swelled with pride when winning the Intel AI Global \u000d\u000aCompetition allowed him to present BhashaX to Intel's CEO. \"Standing there, sharing my vision with global executives, I realized \u000d\u000atechnology's true power to connect people,\" says Krish. His work was also showcased at Impact Fest and Intel\u2019s Silicon Valley \u000d\u000aHeadquarters, reinforcing AI\u2019s potential for societal impact.\u000d\u000aNow at Napo University, Krish is integrating large-scale language models to enhance BhashaX while building AI-driven startups and \u000d\u000amentoring young enthusiasts. \"Technology should unite us, not divide us,\" says Krish. Through BhashaX, Krish isn't just translating \u000d\u000acode\u2014he's translating opportunity, one language at a time. ","Fear of numbers is real. For Oushneek Nath, mathematics \u000d\u000aonce sparked anxiety more than curiosity. Like many \u000d\u000astudents, complex formulas and abstract theories deterred \u000d\u000ahim from engaging deeply in the subject. But discovering the \u000d\u000aAISC platform in 2023 changed everything, igniting a \u000d\u000apassion for AI that transformed his relationship with numbers.\u000d\u000aMonths of coding, experimenting with AI tools, and relentless \u000d\u000alearning led to his breakthrough insight. The fundamental \u000d\u000aflaw in math education was prioritizing memorization over \u000d\u000aunderstanding. \u000d\u000aMathmateX emerged as his solution, an AI-powered platform \u000d\u000amaking mathematics accessible to everyone, including those \u000d\u000awith disabilities like dyscalculia. Integrating AI-driven error \u000d\u000adetection, symbolic computation, and real-time graphing, \u000d\u000aMathmateX offers precise, step-by-step solutions and \u000d\u000avisualizations that bring math concepts to life. The platform \u000d\u000aaligns with SDG 4 (Quality Education) by making math \u000d\u000alearning inclusive and SDG 10 (Reduced Inequalities) by \u000d\u000aoffering accessible tools for diverse learning needs.\u000d\u000aUNLOCKING\u000d\u000aMATH\u000d\u000aFOR ALL\u000d\u000aTHE INSPIRING JOURNEY\u000d\u000aBEHIND MATHMATEX\u000d\u000aFrom math phobia to AI innovation\u2014 Oushneek\u2019s \u000d\u000aquest to revolutionize learning for global inclusion \u000d\u000aand empowerment.","Oushneek's journey reached new heights when he won the 2024 India AI Impact \u000d\u000aFestival. This victory connected him with industry mentors who helped refine \u000d\u000aMathmateX's interface and expand its capabilities. \"Without the Intel AI program, \u000d\u000aI would have remained stuck in the basics, unaware of AI's potential. The \u000d\u000astructured guidance and expert mentorship gave me confidence to build and \u000d\u000aenhance MathmateX,\" he acknowledges.\u000d\u000aWhile MathmateX has yet to be officially released, Oushneek is dreaming big. He \u000d\u000aenvisions expanding its capabilities to reverse-engineer graphs into equations\u2014a \u000d\u000afeature that could revolutionize problem-solving approaches. Now in 10th grade, \u000d\u000ahis passion for AI drives new projects too, such as Crescendo, an app that \u000d\u000aanalyzes vocals to replicate musical sounds.\u000d\u000aThis youngster\u2019s journey is a testament to how education and emerging \u000d\u000atechnology can empower students to turn fear into innovation and create \u000d\u000asolutions that can change lives.\u000d\u000aOushneek Nath\u000d\u000aDelhi Public School\u000d\u000aElectronic city,\u000d\u000aBengaluru, Karnataka","REVOLUTIONIZING\u000d\u000aWATER\u000d\u000aCONSERVATION\u000d\u000aWITH AI\u000d\u000aA high school innovator, harnesses AI to \u000d\u000amake every drop count and empower \u000d\u000afarmers through smart technology\u000d\u000a\u201cWater scarcity threatens agriculture,\u201d says Dhruv Kumar. \u000d\u000a\u201cFarmers struggle to manage irrigation, detect leaks, and \u000d\u000aharvest rainwater, costing them financially and harming the \u000d\u000aenvironment.\u201d Witnessing these issues firsthand, Dhruv \u000d\u000aknew he had to act.\u000d\u000a\"Sometimes we water too much, sometimes too little,\" a \u000d\u000agardener confessed during Dhruv's survey, revealing the \u000d\u000aheart of the issue. Inspired by India Water Week in New Delhi \u000d\u000aand observing similar issues in city drainage systems, Dhruv \u000d\u000aenvisioned an AI-powered solution for farmers.\u000d\u000aDhruv\u2019s AI journey began in 2020 during the COVID-19 \u000d\u000alockdown when he got his first laptop and started \u000d\u000aresearching and learning about AI. His passion grew by 2022 \u000d\u000aafter he attended Intel\u2019s AI program, where he gained \u000d\u000astructured knowledge and mentorship from experts.","In 2023, he specialized in computer vision at an AI boot camp, \u000d\u000aand by 2024, he had won multiple AI research competitions, \u000d\u000apublished three research papers, and delivered tech talks at \u000d\u000aGoogle, Microsoft, and TEDx events. His research also earned \u000d\u000ahim a gold medal from Bennett University.\u000d\u000aHis breakthrough innovation\u2014W-A RC\u2014is an AI and \u000d\u000aIoT-integrated water management system with four key tools: \u000d\u000aan AI-based irrigation predictor, a leak detection system using \u000d\u000aacoustic and pressure sensors, a rainwater harvester predictor, \u000d\u000aand a scenario generator using GAN models to help farmers \u000d\u000achoose crops wisely.\u000d\u000aNow in high school, Dhruv works as an AI engineer at AI Planet, \u000d\u000aa Belgium-based startup. He's developing a Hindi-speaking AI \u000d\u000aassistant using Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to \u000d\u000aoffer real-time guidance for rural farmers, bridging the \u000d\u000alanguage and technology. \u000d\u000aCurrently refining W-A RC, Dhruv aims to make it more \u000d\u000aaccessible for farmers. \"I want to work in AI innovation and do \u000d\u000aprojects with a bigger impact,\" he says, his eyes gleaming with \u000d\u000ahope. His vision: a future where AI helps farmers conserve water, \u000d\u000aboost crop yields, and protect the planet\u2014one drop at a time.\u000d\u000aDhruv Kumar\u000d\u000aDr. Rajendra Prasad\u000d\u000aKendriya Vidyalaya,\u000d\u000aDelhi","When the founders of Sporty Coach first met during a school \u000d\u000ainnovation challenge in 2021, they shared one frustration\u2014\u000d\u000asports training in India often lacked personalized guidance. \u000d\u000aCoaches were stretched thin, resources were limited, and \u000d\u000ayoung athletes rarely got feedback that matched their unique \u000d\u000astrengths and weaknesses. \u201cWe saw our friends giving up on \u000d\u000asports simply because they didn\u2019t get the right mentoring,\u201d \u000d\u000arecalls one of the makers.\u000d\u000aTheir curiosity turned into commitment when they joined the \u000d\u000aIntel AI for Youth program. Exposure to AI\u2019s potential opened \u000d\u000atheir eyes to how technology could transform training. With \u000d\u000amentorship and hands-on practice, they designed Sporty \u000d\u000aCoach, an AI-powered application that analyzes player \u000d\u000amovements, detects posture errors, and suggests \u000d\u000aimprovements in real time. Using computer vision models \u000d\u000aoptimized with Intel\u2019s OpenVINO toolkit, the system captures \u000d\u000avideo of practice sessions and delivers instant feedback\u2014\u000d\u000aalmost like having a personal coach on the field 24/7.\u000d\u000aTurning passion into performance, Sporty Coach is \u000d\u000aredefining how young athletes train, learn, and thrive.\u000d\u000aSPORTY\u000d\u000aCOACH\u000d\u000aSHAPING\u000d\u000aTOMORROW\u2019S\u000d\u000aATHLETES WITH\u000d\u000aAI AND HEART","But Sporty Coach is more than an app; it\u2019s a mission. To ensure inclusivity, the \u000d\u000ateam trained the model across multiple sports and diverse datasets so that even \u000d\u000astudents from rural schools could benefit. Pilot testing in community grounds \u000d\u000ashowed a marked improvement in performance, with young athletes reporting \u000d\u000ahigher confidence and motivation.\u000d\u000aThe project soon gained recognition, being showcased at the Intel AI Global \u000d\u000aImpact Festival, where it stood out for its blend of social purpose and technical \u000d\u000ainnovation. \u201cIt was surreal presenting Sporty Coach to a global jury\u2014we realized \u000d\u000awe weren\u2019t just building software, we were building futures,\u201d says the team.\u000d\u000aLooking ahead, the makers plan to expand Sporty Coach into a comprehensive \u000d\u000aplatform\u2014integrating nutrition guidance, injury prevention analytics, and \u000d\u000aAI-driven performance tracking. Their dream is simple yet powerful: every child, \u000d\u000ano matter where they are from, deserves the chance to play better, dream bigger, \u000d\u000aand grow stronger.\u000d\u000aThrough Sporty Coach, these young innovators are proving that technology isn\u2019t \u000d\u000ajust about winning\u2014it\u2019s about unlocking human potential, one athlete at a time.\u000d\u000aArjun Manocha\u000d\u000aSwasti Sharma\u000d\u000aArham Jain\u000d\u000aDarbari Lal DAV \u000d\u000aModel School, \u000d\u000aPitampura, Rohini, \u000d\u000aDelhi","","FOR FUTURE A WORKFORCE\u000d\u000aHIGHER EDUCATION","In 2022, three friends\u2014Yatharth Wazir, Yashkumar Dubey, and Tanisha \u000d\u000aKaur\u2014found themselves captivated by the possibilities of computers. \u000d\u000aTanisha\u2019s journey began in fourth grade, designing presentations, \u000d\u000awhile Yatharth and Yashkumar dived into programming in college. \u000d\u000aThough artificial intelligence initially seemed intimidating, they soon \u000d\u000arecognized its potential to drive meaningful change.\u000d\u000aThe inspiring journey of three students who used AI to turn\u000d\u000asign language into a powerful tool for inclusion and connection.\u000d\u000aISHAARA\u000d\u000aGIVING VOICE TO SILENCE\u000d\u000aYatharth Wazir\u000d\u000aYashkumar Dubey\u000d\u000aTanisha Kaur\u000d\u000aKJ Somaiya Institute of \u000d\u000aTechnology, Mumbai, \u000d\u000aMaharashtra","Their brainstorming led to an AI-powered interpreter bridging Indian Sign Language (ISL) with text and speech. \u000d\u000aWithout structured guidance, progress was uncertain\u2014until they discovered CBSE\u2019s AI Student Community. \u000d\u000aWith mentorship from their professor and support from Intel India, Ishaara evolved into a sophisticated system \u000d\u000aintegrating audio processing, NLP for 108 languages, deep learning, and computer vision for ISL recognition.\u000d\u000aFacing the challenge of non-existent ISL datasets, they painstakingly created their own by recording gesture \u000d\u000avideos\u2014transforming Ishaara into a labor of love. Intel's OpenVINO toolkit dramatically improved efficiency, \u000d\u000areducing response time to just 0.1 seconds.\u000d\u000aIshaara's impact resonated widely, winning national and global recognition at AI Impact Festivals, Dell AI Thon, \u000d\u000aAvishkar Competition, and the International Student Research Convention. The project was showcased before \u000d\u000aIntel executives and the Minister of Skill Development in Delhi in November 2024.\u000d\u000aLooking ahead, the team aims to expand Ishaara to support American and British Sign Languages, collaborate \u000d\u000awith NGOs, and launch APIs and a YouTube sign-language avatar extension. As Yatharth and Yashkumar pursue \u000d\u000amaster\u2019s degrees and Tanisha steps into her tech career, their vision remains clear.\u000d\u000a\"Ishaara is more than a project\u2014it\u2019s our way of bringing inclusivity to the world,\u201d says Tanisha. \u201cNo one should feel \u000d\u000aleft out because of how they communicate.\u201d What began as a college project is now a movement, breaking \u000d\u000acommunication barriers and making the world more accessible.","In the bustling town of Hosur, Tamil Nadu, Sujan Saitej stumbled upon \u000d\u000asomething that would alter his life\u2019s trajectory\u2014an Instagram reel \u000d\u000aabout Intel\u2019s AI for Youth program. \u000d\u000aDespite having no prior knowledge of artificial intelligence, machine \u000d\u000alearning, or building AI models, something about the possibility of \u000d\u000acreating technology that could solve real problems ignited a spark \u000d\u000awithin him, and he registered for the program.\u000d\u000a\u201cThose 14 days changed everything,\u201d Sujan recalls, his voice filled with \u000d\u000athe unmistakable excitement of someone who has found their calling. \u000d\u000a\u201cI realized the true potential of technology in solving real-world \u000d\u000aproblems. It opened my eyes that AI is a tool that could drive \u000d\u000ameaningful change.\u201d\u000d\u000aGradually, Sujan began experimenting with deepfake technology and \u000d\u000asaw an opportunity to harness its power for education. His first major \u000d\u000aproject, TUTOLESS-AI, used deepfake technology to create virtual \u000d\u000atutors, making learning interactive and engaging for students. \u000d\u000aHowever, he also recognized a darker side of it\u2014deepfake videos \u000d\u000awere being misused to spread misinformation, target public figures, \u000d\u000aand erode trust in digital content. \u000d\u000aVerifiAi chronicles the inspiring journey of \u000d\u000aSujan Saitej, who transformed deepfake \u000d\u000atechnology from a potential threat into a \u000d\u000apowerful shield for truth.\u000d\u000aVERIFIAI\u000d\u000aRESTORING TRUST\u000d\u000aIN THE DIGITAL AGE","This realization led him to create VerifiAi, a deepfake detection tool, \u000d\u000apowered by advanced deep learning models. VerifiAi distinguishes \u000d\u000abetween authentic and manipulated content with remarkable accuracy \u000d\u000ausing ResNeXt for feature extraction and long short-term memory \u000d\u000anetworks for temporal analysis.\u000d\u000aThe innovation quickly earned recognition, garnering Sujan the Intel AI \u000d\u000afor Youth Excellence Award and a state-level AI Innovation Award. \u000d\u000aToday, as he pursues his Bachelor of Technology in Information \u000d\u000aTechnology at Saveetha School of Engineering, Chennai, Sujan is the \u000d\u000afounder of DiffuseAi, a startup focused on educational technology. \u000d\u000aSelected from 6,000 applicants for IIT\u2019s prestigious incubation \u000d\u000aprogram, he continues to expand his vision.\u000d\u000a\u201cTechnology should serve truth and learning,\u201d Sujan reflects. \u201cIn a world \u000d\u000awhere seeing is no longer believing, we need tools that help us \u000d\u000arecognize reality.\u201d\u000d\u000aSujan Saitej\u000d\u000aSaveetha Institute of \u000d\u000aMedical & Technical \u000d\u000aSciences, Chennai, \u000d\u000aTamil Nadu","Aditya Saroj\u000d\u000aNIELIT,\u000d\u000aKarkardooma, \u000d\u000aDelhi\u000d\u000aDriven by a passion for AI, Aditya developed an intelligent \u000d\u000atool for smart surveillance for a safer world.\u000d\u000aAI BREAKTHROUGH\u000d\u000aIN INTRUDER\u000d\u000aDETECTION","Aditya's journey into artificial intelligence began with a \u000d\u000asimple question: \"How can we know who\u2014or what\u2014is \u000d\u000aentering our spaces?\" \u000d\u000aIt wasn\u2019t until he joined the Intel AI for Future Workforce \u000d\u000aprogram that this interest turned into purpose. The \u000d\u000aprogram didn\u2019t just teach him tools\u2014it lit a fire, giving \u000d\u000ahim the platform to transform imagination into \u000d\u000ainnovation. The Intel program provided structured \u000d\u000aguidance, real-world projects, and peer collaboration, \u000d\u000awhich was his springboard to dive deep into machine \u000d\u000alearning and data science. \u000d\u000aOne of his standout projects\u2014Intruder Detection\u2014was \u000d\u000aborn out of a desire to solve a common problem: \u000d\u000adistinguishing whether a being entering a space is \u000d\u000ahuman or animal. \"This program can determine whether \u000d\u000athe intruder entering is an animal or a human,\" Aditya \u000d\u000aexplains with enthusiasm. \u000d\u000aWhat makes Aditya's work remarkable is its accessibility. \u000d\u000aRather than relying on complex programming \u000d\u000alanguages that might intimidate novice developers, he \u000d\u000abuilt his solution using Orange Data Mining, a tool that \u000d\u000aprocesses collected data to identify distinguishing \u000d\u000afeatures between humans and animals. \"For humans, \u000d\u000ahaving two legs and two hands becomes a feature; our \u000d\u000aheight becomes a feature. For animals, having four legs \u000d\u000abecomes a feature,\" he explains. \"This will become an \u000d\u000aautomatic tech security system,\" Aditya notes, \u000d\u000adescribing how zoo managers could automate \u000d\u000aresponses when animals attempt to leave their \u000d\u000aenclosures.\u000d\u000aToday, Aditya continues to expand his AI expertise \u000d\u000athrough his BCA studies while refining his AI knowledge \u000d\u000ain the AI Development Associate program at NIELIT. \u000d\u000aHis story is a reminder that with the right opportunity, a \u000d\u000aspark of interest can ignite a lifelong pursuit. The Intel \u000d\u000aprogram didn\u2019t just teach Aditya AI; it gave him the \u000d\u000aconfidence to shape a safer, smarter world.","An inspirational story of a non-tech student turned a \u000d\u000asimple idea into AI-powered glasses to help ease the \u000d\u000alife of the visually impaired.\u000d\u000aILLUMINATING\u000d\u000aTHE DARK\u000d\u000aTHE AI GLASSES\u000d\u000aREVOLUTION\u000d\u000aWithout the Intel-backed India AI Data Lab and its mentorship, \u000d\u000athis vision might have remained just an idea. \u201cI got every step, all \u000d\u000athe support\u2026 and the most important, Intel's experts' guidance \u000d\u000aand mentoring.\u201d Atul worked tirelessly, often through the night, \u000d\u000adetermined to bring his prototype to life. \u201cFinally, I have my \u000d\u000aAI-powered glasses prototype, a project that can make the lives \u000d\u000aof visually-impaired people a little easier.\u201d\u000d\u000aThe impact didn\u2019t stop there. \u201cMy sister, who is from a \u000d\u000acommerce background, has also taken admission here, and is \u000d\u000aworking on an AI-enabled social impact project,\u201d he continues \u000d\u000awith pride. \u000d\u000aToday, Atul is preparing to launch a startup focused on inclusive \u000d\u000aAI products, proving that when opportunity meets purpose, \u000d\u000areal-world change follows.","Atul Kirar\u000d\u000aLife had hit a lull for Atul Kirar, a student from a Humanities \u000d\u000abackground, until destiny quietly arrived through the pages of a \u000d\u000anewspaper. \u201cAfter passing grade 12 exams, I was feeling lost and \u000d\u000acouldn\u2019t find the right path ahead. Then, one day, my dad saw an \u000d\u000aad for the government-approved NIELIT AI Development \u000d\u000aAssociate Course in the newspaper.\u201d \u000d\u000aDespite having no technical background, the young innovator \u000d\u000aembraced the challenge of mastering both coding and no-code \u000d\u000aAI tools. However, the search for a meaningful project led to a \u000d\u000amoment of inspiration. Witnessing a visually impaired person \u000d\u000astruggling sparked an idea that would become revolutionary. \u000d\u000aThis is when Atul decided to create AI-powered glasses to assist \u000d\u000athose with vision impairment.\u000d\u000a\"It was a challenge for me. I was working on it without seeing day \u000d\u000aand night,\" shares the creator about the development process \u000d\u000athat demanded unwavering dedication. This perseverance \u000d\u000aeventually resulted in a working prototype designed to make the \u000d\u000alives of visually impaired people easier.\u000d\u000aNIELIT,\u000d\u000aKarkardooma, \u000d\u000aDelhi","Karishma and \u000d\u000aShikha\u000d\u000aTwo young minds, Karishma and Shikha, use technology to nurture mental wellbeing \u000d\u000awhen productivity overshadows happiness.\u000d\u000aSMILES DECODED\u000d\u000aTHE AI-POWERED HAPPINESS INDEX\u000d\u000aNIELIT,\u000d\u000aKarkardooma, Delhi","\u201cCan technology understand how we feel?\u201d As young learners \u000d\u000aenrolled in the Level 1 AI course at NIELIT, Karishma and \u000d\u000aShikha\u2019s exploration of AI wasn\u2019t just academic, but personal.\u000d\u000aTheir shared interest in computers gradually evolved into a \u000d\u000apassion for using technology to solve human problems, \u000d\u000aparticularly those often overlooked in our productivity-driven \u000d\u000aworld. \"We noticed that in schools and workplaces, our focus \u000d\u000atends to be more on productivity and achieving targets. \u000d\u000aBecause of this, we often ignore our mental wellbeing, mental \u000d\u000ahealth, and overall happiness,\" reflects Karishma.\u000d\u000aThe Intel AI program gave them the critical resources to \u000d\u000atransform their ideas into reality. Using a pre-trained Intel AI \u000d\u000amodel trained on hundreds of thousands of images, they built a \u000d\u000aprototype to detect a person\u2019s emotional state from their facial \u000d\u000aexpressions. If the system recognized signs of low happiness, it \u000d\u000arecommended recreational or mental health-boosting activities. \u000d\u000a\u201cOur model doesn\u2019t just read emotions\u2014it responds with \u000d\u000aempathy,\u201d Shikha said.\u000d\u000aBut what if the Intel program hadn\u2019t existed? \u201cHonestly, \u000d\u000awithout it, we might have never realized AI could be so \u000d\u000ahuman,\u201d said Karishma. The Intel AI initiative wasn\u2019t just a \u000d\u000alearning platform\u2014it was a launchpad. Before the \u000d\u000aprogram, they were interested in tech; after the program, \u000d\u000athey were committed to using it for social good.\u000d\u000aToday, Karishma is pursuing a career in AI-driven health\u000d\u000atech, focusing on mental wellness tools for young adults. \u000d\u000aHowever, Shikha is working as a data analyst, using \u000d\u000amachine learning to improve user experience in \u000d\u000aeducational platforms. Their paths may differ, but the \u000d\u000agoal remains united: make technology more human.\u000d\u000a\u201cAI isn\u2019t just about machines,\u201d Shikha says. \u201cIt\u2019s about \u000d\u000aunderstanding people better\u2014and helping them thrive.\u201d","Ananya\u000d\u000aHow Ananya\u2019s AI-powered app transforms \u000d\u000athe uncertainty and investing game for \u000d\u000abeginners, one investor at a time. FORECASTING\u000d\u000aFUTURES\u000d\u000aANANYA\u2019S AI-POWERED\u000d\u000aSTOCK MARKET VISION\u000d\u000a\"The stock market terrifies most beginners, and I \u000d\u000awanted to change that,\" says 19-year-old \u000d\u000aAnanya. Her journey with artificial intelligence \u000d\u000abegan not with a textbook, but with a friend\u2019s \u000d\u000astruggle. \u201cAdit tried investing in the stock market \u000d\u000alast month, but he faced a lot of difficulties,\u201d she \u000d\u000arecalled. This sparked a powerful idea: What if AI \u000d\u000acould help beginners like Adit make smarter, \u000d\u000asafer investments?\u000d\u000aNIELIT, \u000d\u000aKarkardooma, \u000d\u000aDelhi","Ananya was pursuing a Bachelor of Commerce degree, but her \u000d\u000apassion for AI truly ignited when she joined the Intel AI for Youth \u000d\u000aprogram. It wasn't just a course\u2014it was the turning point for her. \u000d\u000a\u201cBefore this, I was curious,\u201d she said. \u201cBut the Intel program gave \u000d\u000ame the direction, the mentorship, and the courage to actually build \u000d\u000asomething real.\u201d\u000d\u000aHer stock market prediction application stands out by claiming to \u000d\u000a\"reduce risk by 90%\" through advanced predictive analytics. \u000d\u000aThat\u2019s not all! The intuitive interface features live charts, \u000d\u000ahistograms, and detailed information on major indices like the \u000d\u000aSensex and Nifty IT. Users can browse through 15+ companies or \u000d\u000aupload CSV files for customized predictions. \u000d\u000a\"If you wish to invest in a particular company,\" Ananya demonstrates, \"the app will tell you the \u000d\u000apredicted share prices for the future, how much you should invest, and what returns you can expect in \u000d\u000aa defined timeline.\"\u000d\u000aToday, Ananya continues integrating her commerce education with AI expertise, developing financial \u000d\u000atechnology solutions that democratize investing. By making market analysis accessible to beginners, \u000d\u000ashe's building a career at the intersection of finance and AI, empowering hesitant investors to make \u000d\u000aconfident decisions through data-driven insights. Her dream? To build smarter, safer digital financial \u000d\u000atools for all. In her own words: \u201cAI isn\u2019t the future anymore. It\u2019s the present\u2014and I want to shape it.\u201d","Rishikesh Amit \u000d\u000aNayak\u000d\u000aVellore Institute of \u000d\u000aTechnology , Chennai, \u000d\u000aTamil Nadu\u000d\u000aRishikesh Amit Nayak\u2019s innovation, Kishan Know, is an AI-powered precision \u000d\u000afarming system that predicts crop threats, detects soil and pest issues in real \u000d\u000atime, and delivers affordable, scalable solutions\u2014empowering small farmers \u000d\u000aand transforming rural agriculture in India.\u000d\u000aKISHAN KNOW\u000d\u000aAI-POWERED HOPE FOR INDIA\u2019S\u000d\u000aAGRICULTURAL COMMUNITY\u000d\u000aIn the quiet fields of Repur Patna, Odisha, young Rishikesh \u000d\u000aAmit Nayak watched his community wrestle with nature\u2019s \u000d\u000aunpredictability\u2014droughts, pests, and the silent weight of \u000d\u000adebt. When a close relative tragically succumbed to \u000d\u000afarm-related distress, it left more than grief\u2014it ignited a \u000d\u000aresolve to transform the future of farming in India.\u000d\u000aRishikesh's journey into technology began in middle \u000d\u000aschool with simple IoT and robotics projects. However, it \u000d\u000awas his participation in Intel\u2019s AI for Youth program in 2019 \u000d\u000athat transformed his curiosity into capability. The program \u000d\u000aprovided the mentorship and technical guidance that \u000d\u000awould later fuel his groundbreaking agricultural innovation.","As alarming reports of farmer suicides mounted in 2017, Rishikesh and his team at Vellore \u000d\u000aInstitute of Technology developed Kishan Know, an AI-powered precision farming system. \u000d\u000aBuilt using Intel\u00ae OpenVINO\u2122 technology, this system deploys drones and thermal imagery \u000d\u000ato analyze soil health and detect early signs of disease, empowering farmers to act before \u000d\u000acrisis hits. \u000d\u000aA real-world validation that cemented Kishan Know\u2019s importance came in 2021, when it \u000d\u000aaccurately predicted a plant disease outbreak across 13 villages. Farmers who heeded the \u000d\u000awarnings saved their crops, while skeptics suffered devastating losses.\u000d\u000a\u201cThe most powerful aspect of Kishan Know is its accessibility,\u201d Rishikesh explains. \u201cWe've \u000d\u000adesigned the technology to cost less than a dollar, ensuring even small and marginal farmers \u000d\u000acan benefit.\u201d\u000d\u000aRecognized as the global winner at the Intel AI Global \u000d\u000aImpact Festival 2021, Rishikesh now aims to expand \u000d\u000ahis innovation into aquaculture and impact one million \u000d\u000aagricultural families across India in the next two years.\u000d\u000aAs he approaches graduation with a B.Tech in \u000d\u000aMechatronics and Automation, Rishikesh remains \u000d\u000afocused on his mission. \u000d\u000aIn the verdant fields of rural India, farmers are \u000d\u000abeginning to harvest not just crops, but hope\u2014thanks \u000d\u000ato a young innovator who transformed personal \u000d\u000atragedy into a technological lifeline for those who feed \u000d\u000athe nation.","Rahul \u000d\u000aJaikrishna \u000d\u000aRahul Biliyar\u000d\u000aPES University, \u000d\u000aBengaluru, Karnataka\u000d\u000aRahul Jaikrishna and Rahul Biliyar\u2019s innovation, WildSense, \u000d\u000ahelps mitigate human-wildlife conflicts by detecting animals \u000d\u000aon wildlife corridors and issuing real-time \u000d\u000awarnings\u2014safeguarding both travelers and wildlife.\u000d\u000aWILDSENSE\u000d\u000aAN AI-POWERED\u000d\u000aGUARDIAN OF INDIA\u2019S\u000d\u000aWILDLIFE CORRIDORS\u000d\u000aIn India, where busy highways cut through wildlife \u000d\u000ahabitats, a tragic reality persists\u2014over 400,000 \u000d\u000aanimals die annually on roads, according to WWF \u000d\u000astudies. Amidst this crisis, two innovative \u000d\u000aengineering students have developed a solution that \u000d\u000acould save countless lives.\u000d\u000aRahul Jaikrishna's journey into AI began in 2019 \u000d\u000awhen he developed Cyber Detective, an AI tool that \u000d\u000adetects cyberbullying on Twitter. In 2023, he met \u000d\u000aRahul Biliyar at PES University, Bengaluru, where \u000d\u000athey bonded over their shared concern for wildlife.\u000d\u000aThe duo created WildSense, an AI-powered system \u000d\u000athat detects animals using infrared cameras and alerts \u000d\u000adrivers through LED signboards positioned \u000d\u000a500\u20131000 meters ahead. The patent-pending \u000d\u000atechnology also integrates with Google Maps to \u000d\u000aprovide real-time notifications to approaching drivers. \u000d\u000a\u201cOur solution respects nature\u2019s rhythms\u2014it doesn't \u000d\u000aprevent animals from crossing but ensures safer \u000d\u000aroads by warning drivers in time,\u201d they explain. \u000d\u000aBeyond wildlife protection, WildSense could benefit \u000d\u000atransportation by keeping roads operational during \u000d\u000ahigh animal activity periods."," The development process wasn\u2019t easy\u2014there were \u000d\u000adata processing issues, visibility challenges, limited \u000d\u000aconnectivity, and potential equipment damage by \u000d\u000aelephants. However, with guidance from Intel mentors, \u000d\u000athey leveraged Intel's OpenVINO toolkit and optimized \u000d\u000aOpenCV to enable real-time deep learning inference \u000d\u000aeven in isolated regions.\u000d\u000a Their innovation was recognized at the Intel AI Impact \u000d\u000aFestival 2024 in the Impact Creators category and \u000d\u000ahighlighted by Intel India's Vice President at the Global \u000d\u000aAI Conclave 2024, broadcast on CNBC.\u000d\u000a Currently in their fourth semester of a computer \u000d\u000ascience engineering degree, the young engineers are \u000d\u000acollaborating with wildlife experts and the Forest Department \u000d\u000ato launch a pilot project in Bannerghatta National Park, \u000d\u000aBengaluru. Their long-term vision includes securing a seed \u000d\u000agrant and government approval to implement WildSense \u000d\u000anationwide.\u000d\u000a Their career plans are crystal clear\u2014Rahul Biliyar aims to \u000d\u000aforge a path in sustainable entrepreneurship, while Rahul \u000d\u000aJaikrishna envisions a future in AI research. \u000d\u000a In the delicate dance between technology and nature, \u000d\u000aWildSense stands as a testament to the harmony achievable \u000d\u000awhen technology serves as a steward of nature. And \u000d\u000asomewhere, on a quiet road deep in the wild, animals cross \u000d\u000aroads safely\u2014thanks to two young minds who dared to dream.","Ashish Verma\u000d\u000aIIT, Delhi\u000d\u000aWhere passion meets purpose: One student's transformation \u000d\u000afrom gaming enthusiast to AI innovator changing education \u000d\u000aand beyond.\u000d\u000aAI JOURNEY\u000d\u000aAs a child, Ashish Verma immersed himself in video \u000d\u000agames like PUBG. But everything shifted when his father \u000d\u000achallenged him: \u201cWhy just play games? Why not create \u000d\u000athem?\u201d That simple question planted a seed of innovation.\u000d\u000aBy grade 9, he had ventured into web development. The \u000d\u000apandemic gave him time to dive deep into Generative AI. \u000d\u000aDuring an internship with Aerenous Technocraft, a \u000d\u000aTurkish colleague mentored him, opening doors to \u000d\u000asolving real-world problems with AI. By 2019, he had \u000d\u000abegun developing mobile applications.\u000d\u000aIn 2021, while in grade 11, Ashish noticed a classroom \u000d\u000ainefficiency: his teacher constantly had to walk to the \u000d\u000acomputer or use a remote to change presentation slides.\u000d\u000aThis sparked the idea for PRESCON, an AI-powered \u000d\u000aassistant that uses gesture recognition to control \u000d\u000apresentations effortlessly. Around the same time, India\u2019s \u000d\u000aPM e-vidya initiative fueled his desire to enhance \u000d\u000aeducational content with animation and interactivity. \u000d\u000aFROM GAMING\u000d\u000aTO INNOVATION","In 2022, Ashish pitched his AI ideas directly to India's Prime \u000d\u000aMinister, Shri Narendra Modi. Motivated by this meeting, he started \u000d\u000aAR Prayogshala, developing Navya AI\u2014a text-to-image model \u000d\u000awith over 25K users\u2014and Vyayam Mitra, a Mixed Reality game \u000d\u000aencouraging physical exercise through interactive gaming.\u000d\u000aIntel's Labs Program provided crucial mentorship and validation. \u000d\u000aAshish became an AI for Youth Leader, earning recognition from \u000d\u000aUNESCO, CBSE, and the Minister of Skill Development. \u000d\u000aEncounters with Santosh Vishwanathan, Intel's MD, helped him \u000d\u000arefine his models. Japan Science and Tech invited him to \u000d\u000arepresent India, and he won the Rashtriya Vaigyanik Puraskar, \u000d\u000adelivered talks at prestigious institutions, and became a Global AI \u000d\u000aImpact Festival Winner.\u000d\u000aNow a first-year Engineering Physics student at IIT Delhi, Ashish \u000d\u000ajuggles studies with roles as CTO and Co-founder of Mercylytics \u000d\u000aAI and Fernbio. \u201cMy vision extends beyond revenue. I want to \u000d\u000aprovide tangible value to society and continue refining AI agents \u000d\u000ato bridge hardware and software gaps,\u201d he shares.","","FOR ALL A IMPACT","In a village in Uttar Pradesh, India, a remarkable transformation took place through the efforts of \u000d\u000aDharam Prakash Shukla. Through his participation in the AI for All training, Dharam Prakash \u000d\u000arecognized the untapped potential of AI in revolutionizing \u000d\u000athe way farmers sell their products. Motivated by this \u000d\u000arealization, Dharam Prakash took it upon himself to facilitate \u000d\u000athe AI course for his fellow villagers. With unwavering \u000d\u000adedication, he encouraged them to attend, spreading \u000d\u000aawareness about the opportunities AI could bring to their \u000d\u000alives. Dharam Prakash also extended his support to AI skilling \u000d\u000asessions designed for the students in the village, \u000d\u000ademystifying AI and its potential use to the next generation.\u000d\u000aThanks to Dharam Prakash's efforts, the village witnessed a \u000d\u000awave of technological empowerment. By embracing AI, \u000d\u000afarmers now have the means to sell their products directly, \u000d\u000abypassing middlemen and reaping greater profits. The community as a whole was awakened to the \u000d\u000apossibilities that AI could offer, fostering a brighter future driven by knowledge, opportunity, and \u000d\u000aself-sufficiency.\u000d\u000aBRIDGING THE\u000d\u000aDIGITAL DIVIDE \u000d\u000aHOW A VILLAGER \u000d\u000aTRANSFORMED THE \u000d\u000aCOMMUNITY THROUGH AI ","Nibha, from Chuaan village in Uttar Pradesh, whose journey began \u000d\u000awith Intel's AI for All program, has taken it upon herself to empower \u000d\u000awomen in her community through education and technology.\u000d\u000aShe successfully conducted her session on Artificial Intelligence (AI) \u000d\u000awith 15 women, leaving an inspiring impact on their lives. The session was \u000d\u000afilled with excitement and curiosity as Nibha explained the basics of AI. \u000d\u000aThe women were overjoyed, saying, \"It has been years since we left \u000d\u000aschool, but now you\u2019ve awakened our desire to learn again.\" Their \u000d\u000ahappiness and eagerness to learn were a testament to the transformative \u000d\u000apower of knowledge. One of the women, who didn\u2019t even know how to \u000d\u000awrite her name, began learning with Nibha\u2019s patient guidance to speak \u000d\u000asearch. This moment reflected the small but meaningful steps these \u000d\u000awomen were taking toward self-learning. Real-Life Applications of AI \u000d\u000aNibha emphasized how AI could be integrated into their daily lives. \u000d\u000aThis story isn\u2019t just about introducing AI to the \u000d\u000awomen of Chuaan village\u2014it\u2019s about reigniting \u000d\u000atheir self-confidence and showing them that it\u2019s \u000d\u000anever too late to learn. Nibha\u2019s efforts have \u000d\u000aopened a window of opportunity for these \u000d\u000awomen to see how education and technology \u000d\u000acan simplify and enrich their lives.\u000d\u000a New recipes for cooking.\u000d\u000a Creative sweater designs for weaving.\u000d\u000a Weather forecasts to plan farming and household activities.\u000d\u000a Information about government schemes for women\u2019s welfare.\u000d\u000a Solutions to everyday problems, like healthcare tips or market rates \u000d\u000a for local produce.\u000d\u000aShe showcased how to find:\u000d\u000a\"It has been years since we left school, but \u000d\u000anow you\u2019ve awakened our desire to learn \u000d\u000aagain.\"\u000d\u000aNibha\u000d\u000aChuaan village, Uttar Pradesh","Sumitra is from the Gaya district of Bihar, she shared that When I walked into Soni Didi\u2019s AI session, I didn't know the AI word \u000d\u000anever heard. I had heard of computers and apps, but AI was new. On the first day, Didi explained how AI works in our apps, like \u000d\u000aGoogle Translate, map, weather, and YouTube. It felt amazing to realize I was already using AI without knowing it! She helped me \u000d\u000aregister for the AI course on my phone which is in Hindi. She said that taught each session, what was around us via mobile, in \u000d\u000awhich there was a quiz.\u000d\u000aBy the second day, we learned how AI could solve real problems. My favorite part was exploring an AI-powered app that helps \u000d\u000aimprove spoken English in Gemini. I\u2019ve always been shy about speaking English at school, but now I use the app daily to practice. \u000d\u000aDidi even said, \u201cAI is like a teacher that\u2019s always available.\u201d It gave me so much confidence. Didi encouraged me saying, \u201cIf you can \u000d\u000ause AI, you can build it too.\u201d Now, I\u2019m helping my siblings learn what I\u2019ve learned, and I\u2019ve started studying more about it. \u000d\u000aSumitra\u000d\u000aGaya, Bihar \u000d\u000aI didn\u2019t just learn \u000d\u000aabout AI,\u000d\u000aI learned how to \u000d\u000adream bigger.","Saba, a 27-year-old, transgender from Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh, \u000d\u000aIndia, remembers joining the AI For All training program in \u000d\u000a2021. Her struggles to get an identity of her own had not been \u000d\u000aeasy for her. She reluctantly started the AI For All Program but by \u000d\u000athe end of it, she was full of ideas for a better future for herself and \u000d\u000athe transgender community. She gained more confidence after \u000d\u000acompleting the AI For All program; not just self-confidence but \u000d\u000ashe became more confident in using digital tools. Saba has \u000d\u000aharnessed the power of AI tools to promote healthcare \u000d\u000aawareness in her community, advocate for transgender rights, \u000d\u000aand create inclusive content for social media. She is considered \u000d\u000aan inspiration by her community members.\u000d\u000aTestimonial for Saba: Rajkumar Singh, Program Manager, \u000d\u000aTargeted Intervention, Uttar Pradesh State Aids Control \u000d\u000aSociety (UPSACS): Saba\u2019s impact on my work and the MSM \u000d\u000a(Male sex with Male) community has been truly transformative. \u000d\u000aShe taught us about websites that are safe and what data we \u000d\u000acan ask for and what data we can share. Her commitment to \u000d\u000aidentifying safe websites and leveraging technology for \u000d\u000acommunity empowerment continues to inspire us, and we have \u000d\u000astarted integrating similar technology-based strategies into our \u000d\u000aprograms. We can now disseminate crucial information more \u000d\u000aefficiently and privately, reaching a larger audience within the \u000d\u000aMSM community.","Malik Iqbal Miyan, a rickshaw operator from Thasra village, Gujarat, \u000d\u000aused to struggle to make ends meet. Living hand-to-mouth, his \u000d\u000aearnings were barely sufficient to meet his family\u2019s needs. However, his \u000d\u000alife took a transformative turn in 2021, when he was introduced to the \u000d\u000apotential of AI tools through the \u201cAI for All\u201d campaign in his community.\u000d\u000aPreviously hesitant to take riders to unfamiliar places, Malik now \u000d\u000aconfidently uses Google Maps to navigate even the remotest areas \u000d\u000aand his earnings have increased significantly as \u000d\u000aa result of his newfound confidence and AI \u000d\u000aproficiency. A beaming Malik is happy that he took the \u000d\u000aopportunity to complete the AI for All Program and \u000d\u000aopenly acknowledges its contribution to expanding his \u000d\u000aknowledge, giving him the confidence to use online \u000d\u000aapps responsibly and subsequently improving his \u000d\u000afinancial well-being.","Soma Das, from the serene landscapes of Sepahijala, \u000d\u000aTripura, is a dedicated homemaker and self-help \u000d\u000agroup member, who embarked on a transformative \u000d\u000ajourney through the AI for All course.\u000d\u000aThis empowering initiative helped her to understand \u000d\u000aand appreciate the possibilities of artificial intelligence \u000d\u000ain everyday life. Soma learnt to seamlessly optimize \u000d\u000ahousehold tasks as she got to know how to integrate \u000d\u000athe power of AI-driven apps into her daily routine. As a \u000d\u000aself-help group member, she leveraged AI for resource \u000d\u000amanagement and financial planning in her community. \u000d\u000aSoma's advocacy and tech-educational impact within \u000d\u000aher family and community showcases the broader \u000d\u000apotential of AI, empowering homemakers and fostering \u000d\u000atechnological literacy in Sepahijala.","BUILDING THE BACKBONE OF A\u000d\u000aFuture-Ready Education Ecosystem\u000d\u000aIntel\u00ae \u000d\u000aIntel\u2019s vision for education is rooted in a clear strategic belief: every student deserves \u000d\u000aa PC\u2014a two-way learning device that builds creators, thinkers, and future innovators.\u000d\u000aIn India\u2019s vast education landscape, where only 9% of young learners have access to \u000d\u000aa PC, the opportunity to drive systemic change is immense. Intel steps into this \u000d\u000aopportunity as the orchestrator of an entire ecosystem.\u000d\u000aActing as the catalyst that brings the entire education ecosystem together, Intel is \u000d\u000aworking closely with education ISVs to build deeper, more interactive learning \u000d\u000asolutions on the PC; with OEM partners to make devices accessible across \u000d\u000asegments; and with retail partners to ensure these solutions reach every learner who \u000d\u000aneeds them.\u000d\u000aIntel works closely with government bodies and policymakers to shape the long-term \u000d\u000aarchitecture for AI in education\u2014aligning with NEP 2020, supporting national digital \u000d\u000ainitiatives, and helping create frameworks that prepare students for an AI-powered \u000d\u000afuture.\u000d\u000a\u0018'1.5&'\u029e3'(2\u029e5-(\u0295#\"\u029efi//1.fi!'<\u029e\u000b-3#+\u029e31fi-2$.1,2\u029efi\u029e$1fi&,#-3#\"\u029e+fi-\"2!fi/#\u029e(-3.\u029efi\u000d\u000aconnected, future-ready education ecosystem\u2014one where every student has the \u000d\u000aright device, and the right support, to shape their own future.","Gignaati\u000d\u000aEmpowering Every Student\u000d\u000ato Become an AI Creator\u000d\u000aGignaati turns the Intel AI PC into a personal AI lab, where students don\u2019t \u000d\u000ajust chat with AI\u2014they actually build AI agents that work for them. With \u000d\u000aits no-code, offline- first Agentic AI Workbench, anyone can quickly \u000d\u000acreate and try AI agents on Intel- powered devices while keeping data \u000d\u000aprivate and performance fast. Students can learn AI basics, build agents \u000d\u000afor real tasks, and discover a marketplace of ready-made AI tools and \u000d\u000agigs, all without writing code. \u000d\u000aBy making advanced AI workflows feel like simple, hands-on projects, \u000d\u000aGignaati and Intel invite every learner to try building their first agent and \u000d\u000astart gaining skills that lead to jobs, side-income as gig workers, and \u000d\u000afuture-ready careers.","HCL GUVI Democratizing AI Skills \u000d\u000afor Every Learner\u000d\u000aHCL GUVI and Intel share a common mission\u2014to make advanced \u000d\u000aAI education accessible to every learner, regardless of language \u000d\u000aor background. By offering AI courses in vernacular languages, \u000d\u000aHCL GUVI breaks long-standing barriers and opens the doors of \u000d\u000aopportunity for students and working professionals across India.\u000d\u000aPowered by Intel, GUVI\u2019s AIML program equips higher-education \u000d\u000alearners and upskilling professionals with industry-ready AI skills \u000d\u000athrough practical, job-aligned training. Learners gain hands-on \u000d\u000aexperience in high-impact domains such as Generative AI, \u000d\u000aAgentic AI, Deep Learning, and MLOps, ensuring they are \u000d\u000aprepared for the roles shaping tomorrow\u2019s workforce.\u000d\u000aTailored for the Intel AI PC, the program blends project-based \u000d\u000alearning with real-world applications, enabling learners to build a \u000d\u000astrong portfolio that demonstrates their capabilities and \u000d\u000aconfidence.\u000d\u000aThrough this collaboration, Intel and HCL GUVI are not just \u000d\u000ateaching AI\u2014they are democratizing it, empowering every learner \u000d\u000ato step into the future with skills that matter.","Infinity Learn\u000d\u000aInfinity Learn and Intel come together with a shared mission: \u000d\u000ato make the PC a true learning companion for every child. \u000d\u000aThrough on-device co-innovation, the teams shaped a \u000d\u000apersonalised, two-way learning experience that supports \u000d\u000astudents anytime, anywhere.\u000d\u000aAs a key innovation by Infinity Learn, AINA runs securely \u000d\u000aon-device, powered by Intel\u2019s AI PC, enabling students with \u000d\u000areal-time mentoring for test prep and for school exams. AINA \u000d\u000ahelps breaks accessibility barriers and introduces AI mentorship in a format that feels natural, inclusive, and truly \u000d\u000astudent-centric, transforming the PC into a smart and trusted \u000d\u000acompanion for every learner\u2019s personal and academic growth.\u000d\u000aPersonalised, \u000d\u000aAlways-On\u000d\u000aLearning for \u000d\u000aEvery K\u201312 \u000d\u000aStudent","PhysicsWallah\u000d\u000aTurning the PC Into a Two-Way Learning Companion\u000d\u000aPhysicsWallah and Intel have partnered to bring a new dimension \u000d\u000aof intelligent, two-way learning to the PC. With its Windows-based \u000d\u000aapp, PhysicsWallah transforms the PC into a powerful creator device\u2014a \u000d\u000aspace where students can learn, explore,question, and grow at their own \u000d\u000apace.\u000d\u000aAt the heart of this experience is AI Guru, a voice-based AI tutor that \u000d\u000aguides students through concepts with clarity and confidence. Designed \u000d\u000ato feel personal and accessible, AI Guru supports both academic understanding and emotional well- being, becoming a steady companion \u000d\u000aduring the highs and lows of learning.\u000d\u000aComplementing this is Saarthi - adapts to each student\u2019s needs\u2014\u000d\u000asimplifying complex ideas, answering doubts instantly, and enabling \u000d\u000alearners to ask questions whenever they need support. As students \u000d\u000aprogress through grades and subjects, Saarthi evolves with them, \u000d\u000aoffering a personalised path that grows as they grow.\u000d\u000aPiFocus by PhysicsWallah: Enabling Safe, Focused Learning for \u000d\u000aYoung Minds\u000d\u000aPiFocus transforms PC into a guardian of focused learning and balanced \u000d\u000adigital habits for children. Built as a Windows-compatible solution, \u000d\u000aPiFocus empowers parents to guide their child\u2019s device usage \u000d\u000aconfidently. With remote controls like app blocking, screen locking, and \u000d\u000aUSB protection, parents can help shape healthy study routines, protect \u000d\u000adevice integrity, and guard against distractions. Real-time insights\u2014such \u000d\u000aas live screen view or usage analytics\u2014offer a window into how children \u000d\u000aengage with digital learning, helping parents intervene wisely, not \u000d\u000aintrusively. By giving families and educators these smart controls, \u000d\u000aPiFocus turn the PC into a trusted partner in a child\u2019s growth journey.","upEducators Empowering Teachers to\u000d\u000aReimagine the Classroom\u000d\u000aIntel and upEducators have partnered to transform the Intel AI PC \u000d\u000ainto a powerful creator device for teachers, educators, and \u000d\u000aparents\u2014bringing intelligent teaching tools directly into their \u000d\u000ahands through the development of upEducate.AI. Enabled to\u000d\u000arun without the internet, upEducate. AI ensures that classrooms \u000d\u000aremain productive, engaging, and uninterrupted\u2014anywhere, \u000d\u000aanytime. \u000d\u000aThe team has created AI-driven features that enhance classroom \u000d\u000aefficiency and make learning more personalised and inclusive. \u000d\u000aThe AI lesson plan generator helps educators design richer, more \u000d\u000acollaborative sessions in minutes, improving learning outcomes \u000d\u000awith ease. With the theme-based lesson planner, teachers can \u000d\u000ainstantly tailor lessons to a child\u2019s interests\u2014turning topics into \u000d\u000astories inspired by themes like cricket, space, or music, making \u000d\u000alearning more relatable and exciting.\u000d\u000aTogether, Intel and upEducators are empowering those who \u000d\u000ashape young minds\u2014helping them teach creatively, adapt quickly, \u000d\u000aand deliver learning experiences that spark curiosity in every \u000d\u000astudent.","Disclaimer: \u00a9 Intel Corporation. Intel, the Intel logo, and other Intel marks are trademarks of Intel Corporation or its subsidiaries. Other \u000d\u000anames and brands may be claimed as the property of others."]